title: Ibis Head
description:
Bronze ibis head. Eyes outlined in silver inlay. Details of beak indicated by incisions. Oblong tang for attachment at base of neck. Cast solid.

Condition: Surface brown and free from pitting. Silver inlay around eyes heavily corroded with considerable portions missing.
credit_line: Gift of Evangeline Wilbour Blashfield, Theodora Wilbour, and Victor Wilbour honoring the wishes of their mother, Charlotte Beebe Wilbour, as a memorial to their father, Charles Edwin Wilbour

labels.content: This bronze ibis head weighs three Egyptian deben (or 9½ ounces), a large expense for the person who commissioned the animal mummy it once decorated.
